Hold on.

480
00:36:01,259 --> 00:36:02,248
Errol, stop moving.

481
00:36:03,127 --> 00:36:04,116
I got nothing.

482
00:36:05,730 --> 00:36:06,788
Santa?

483
00:36:06,998 --> 00:36:08,056
Where am I?

484
00:36:09,667 --> 00:36:11,532
My head.

485
00:36:12,403 --> 00:36:16,999
- I actually did it? I caught Santa Claus.
- Right. It sure looks that way.

486
00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:19,733
Where am I? What's going on here?

487
00:36:19,944 --> 00:36:22,777
Santa Stopper 3, do you copy?

488
00:36:25,383 --> 00:36:26,816
Santa Stopper 2?

489
00:36:30,421 --> 00:36:31,945
Oh, I gotta go get the guys.

490
00:36:32,523 --> 00:36:34,423
I'll be right back. Don't go anywhere.

491
00:36:34,625 --> 00:36:36,593
Ronnie, whatever you do,
don't let him out.

492
00:36:36,794 --> 00:36:39,092
At least not until after
the press conference.

493
00:36:39,297 --> 00:36:43,529
Then we'll show the world that the
magic of Santa Claus really does exist.

494
00:36:43,734 --> 00:36:45,599
Whatever.

495
00:36:52,910 --> 00:36:56,778
I have to admit,
you're the best Santa I've seen yet.

496
00:36:56,981 --> 00:37:00,075
Trevor's clearly gone to a lot of trouble.

497
00:37:00,284 --> 00:37:01,945
Is this real?

498
00:37:02,153 --> 00:37:04,246
Look, pal,
I don't know what he's paying you...

499
00:37:04,455 --> 00:37:06,514
...but it will take more
convincing than this.

500
00:37:06,724 --> 00:37:08,214
You may as well pack up now.

501
00:37:08,426 --> 00:37:10,087
What are you talking about?

502
00:37:10,294 --> 00:37:13,127
You and I both know Trevor
paid you to come here.

503
00:37:13,331 --> 00:37:16,095
- How much?
- Trevor? Trevor Taylor?

504
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:19,030
Is he responsible for this?

505
00:37:19,704 --> 00:37:21,467
Now I get it.

506
00:37:21,672 --> 00:37:25,039
You can tell him,
"Nice try, but no cigar."

507
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:28,542
Tell him I do not,
and never will, believe in Santa.

508
00:37:28,746 --> 00:37:30,111
End of story, done.

509
00:37:30,314 --> 00:37:36,014
You used to believe in me,
Miss Veronica Jean Campbell.

510
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:38,818
- So he told you my name, huh?
- Veronica.

511
00:37:39,023 --> 00:37:41,753
Could he have told me about
a certain Christmas present...

512
00:37:41,959 --> 00:37:44,086
...that a certain girl always wanted...

513
00:37:44,295 --> 00:37:46,695
...but was too embarrassed
to tell anyone about?

514
00:37:46,897 --> 00:37:49,593
- What?
- Here it is, Veronica.

515
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:54,066
A Cuddles, the rainbow-haired, limited
edition magic light-up sparkle wand?

516
00:37:54,272 --> 00:37:56,638
- Merry Christmas.
- How did you...?

517
00:37:56,841 --> 00:37:59,002
But... Oh, my.

518
00:37:59,210 --> 00:38:01,804
You are Santa Claus, aren't you?

519
00:38:02,580 --> 00:38:03,672
You're real!

520
00:38:03,881 --> 00:38:06,748
Santa Claus is real?
I had no idea.

521
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:09,852
- Be quiet, will you?
- Sorry, Mr. Claus, sir.

522
00:38:10,054 --> 00:38:12,579
Mr. Claus is my father.
Call me Santa.

523
00:38:12,790 --> 00:38:14,382
And now that we've got
that out of the way...

524
00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:16,685
...could you please
get me out of here?

525
00:38:16,894 --> 00:38:22,924
- I'm kind of on a tight schedule.
- Anything you say, Santa, sir.

526
00:38:25,836 --> 00:38:27,565
Sorry I didn't believe in you.

527
00:38:27,772 --> 00:38:30,366
- Forget about it. It goes with the job.
- Yes, sir.

528
00:38:30,574 --> 00:38:32,439
You can pull that rope over there.

529
00:38:34,211 --> 00:38:37,510
You know, about trapping you like this...

530
00:38:37,715 --> 00:38:40,275
...I just want to say,
I had nothing to do with it.

531
00:38:40,484 --> 00:38:42,850
And he looks just like in the movies.

532
00:38:44,021 --> 00:38:45,010
Ronnie, don't!

533
00:38:47,091 --> 00:38:51,289
- You said you wouldn't let him out.
- Yeah, when I thought he was a fake.

534
00:38:52,029 --> 00:38:53,018
Hey.

535
00:38:53,230 --> 00:38:55,061
Where'd he go?

536
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:58,132
- What did you do with him, Ronnie?
- Me?

537
00:38:58,602 --> 00:39:01,833
- Nothing.
- He must have gone out the window.

538
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:04,901
Spread out. We got to find him.

539
00:39:05,109 --> 00:39:10,570
- You stay here, in case he comes back.
- Oh, no. I'm going with you.

540
00:39:19,123 --> 00:39:20,681
To Woody, the lumberjack.

541
00:39:20,891 --> 00:39:22,358
Thank you Woodrow.

542
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:28,093
You did what you set out to do, Trev.
Now let him go.

543
00:39:28,299 --> 00:39:30,392
No, no, I still need to call the press.

544
00:39:30,601 --> 00:39:32,831
We need to tell people
the truth once and for all.

545
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:35,062
- He's not getting away.
- Are you crazy?

546
00:39:35,272 --> 00:39:38,332
Santa's got deliveries to make,
a schedule to keep.

547
00:39:38,542 --> 00:39:39,941
What happened to you?

548
00:39:40,144 --> 00:39:45,480
Look, let's just say that maybe,
just maybe, you were right.

549
00:39:45,683 --> 00:39:49,346
- Keep talking.
- What? Do I have to apologize?

550
00:39:49,553 --> 00:39:51,316
Look, can't we just let him go?

551
00:39:51,522 --> 00:39:54,457
Are you trying to help Santa get away?
Again?

552
00:39:55,626 --> 00:39:58,390
Now that he's real,
that changes everything.

553
00:39:59,997 --> 00:40:02,261
I think I heard something
inside the shed.

554
00:40:02,466 --> 00:40:04,024
I'll check it out.

555
00:40:07,004 --> 00:40:08,938
Santa?

556
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:10,835
Is that you?

557
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:12,235
Are you in here?

558
00:40:13,811 --> 00:40:15,779
Trevor. What's going on?

559
00:40:15,980 --> 00:40:18,881
Sorry, Ronnie,
but I'm doing this for your own good.

560
00:40:19,083 --> 00:40:21,449
You're gonna interfere
with the rest of the mission.

561
00:40:21,652 --> 00:40:25,144
- Open this door, Trevor.
- Soon as my mission is complete.

562
00:40:25,356 --> 00:40:26,823
You have my word as a friend.

563
00:40:27,024 --> 00:40:28,616
No, right now.

564
00:40:28,826 --> 00:40:32,626
I can't trust you to follow orders,
and this is bigger than the both of us.

565
00:40:32,830 --> 00:40:35,390
- Oh, I'm gonna get you for this.
- You.

566
00:40:36,133 --> 00:40:37,998
You put me behind schedule.

567
00:40:38,736 --> 00:40:40,727
Santa, I know you're upset.

568
00:40:40,938 --> 00:40:42,872
I didn't mean for it to go down like this.

569
00:40:43,073 --> 00:40:44,233
Get him.

570
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:46,637
- Look, I'm a busy guy.
- Let him go.

571
00:40:47,244 --> 00:40:48,302
Please, Santa.

572
00:40:48,512 --> 00:40:51,379
All I wanted was to show
everyone that you exist.

573
00:40:51,582 --> 00:40:53,015
You know, for real life.

574
00:40:53,484 --> 00:40:56,419
- It'll only take a few minutes.
- Do you know what you've done?

575
00:40:56,620 --> 00:40:59,418
I have to clear Greenland
before the sun comes up.

576
00:40:59,623 --> 00:41:06,085
Mr. Claus, all I'm asking for
is a teeny little press conference.

577
00:41:06,297 --> 00:41:09,323
How about we settle for a photograph?

578
00:41:17,541 --> 00:41:18,940
I don't feel so good.

579
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:22,510
- What is that?
- Trevor, my boy.

580
00:41:22,713 --> 00:41:25,011
I think you've now become
the least of my problems.

581
00:41:25,216 --> 00:41:28,777
Okay, you kids, stay close to me.
Things are about to get a little chilly.

582
00:41:28,986 --> 00:41:32,786
This would've been a good
year for gift certificates.

583
00:41:33,991 --> 00:41:37,620
Bedford Falls, Welton Mountain...

584
00:41:37,828 --> 00:41:42,162
...Avenly, Meisterburger Village?

585
00:41:42,366 --> 00:41:46,735
- We're miles off course.
- We're lucky to be alive, trainee.

586
00:41:46,937 --> 00:41:50,168
We're off schedule,
stuck in the middle of nowhere...

587
00:41:50,374 --> 00:41:51,898
...and we've lost our captain.

588
00:41:52,910 --> 00:41:57,904
Saddle up, trainee, this has
just turned into a rescue mission.

589
00:42:13,631 --> 00:42:15,292
Earth.

590
00:42:16,166 --> 00:42:17,599
I haven't been here for a while.

591
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:19,601
It hasn't changed much.

592
00:42:19,803 --> 00:42:21,065
Now, where is he?

593
00:42:21,272 --> 00:42:24,332
He could be anywhere, boss.
Look at this place.

594
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:27,306
Is it warm down here, or is it just me?

595
00:42:27,511 --> 00:42:29,672
It is a little balmy.

596
00:42:30,381 --> 00:42:34,784
I think it's time to get a
little more comfortable. Boys.

597
00:42:36,587 --> 00:42:40,580
Santa, I've had just about
enough of your nonsense.

598
00:42:40,791 --> 00:42:43,919
Now, let me just count the ways.

599
00:42:44,128 --> 00:42:48,258
Five, six, seven, eight!

600
00:42:48,465 --> 00:42:52,094
<i>Santa, I've got a beef with you</i>

601
00:42:52,303 --> 00:42:55,830
<i>Santa, I think you know it too</i>

602
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:59,898
<i>And, Santa, get ready to be Santa who</i>

603
00:43:00,477 --> 00:43:04,470
<i>Because I've got a list</i>
<i>A list of my own</i>

604
00:43:04,682 --> 00:43:06,877
- One!
- Big red baggy pants.

605
00:43:07,084 --> 00:43:08,574
- Two!
- Little elves that dance.

606
00:43:08,786 --> 00:43:10,879
- Three!
- That silly, white beard.

607
00:43:11,088 --> 00:43:12,487
- Four!
- Hey, you're pretty weird.

608
00:43:12,690 --> 00:43:14,214
- Five!
- The mall.

609
00:43:14,959 --> 00:43:16,893
- Six!
- You've got a lot of gall.

610
00:43:17,094 --> 00:43:18,721
- Seven!
- And all those snacks.

611
00:43:18,929 --> 00:43:20,726
- Eight!
- You better watch your back.

612
00:43:20,931 --> 00:43:24,526
<i>Because I've got a list</i>
<i>A list of my own</i>

613
00:43:25,135 --> 00:43:28,400
<i>He's got a list</i>
<i>A list of his own</i>

614
00:43:29,006 --> 00:43:30,530
<i>Because I've got a list</i>

615
00:43:31,108 --> 00:43:32,473
<i>He's got a list</i>

616
00:43:32,676 --> 00:43:37,807
<i>Oh, I've got a list</i>
<i>A list of my</i>

617
00:43:38,015 --> 00:43:43,214
<i>We've got to catch him</i>
<i>We've got to catch Santa Claus</i>

618
00:43:43,420 --> 00:43:45,115
<i>Own</i>

619
00:44:00,304 --> 00:44:02,465
- You know that guy?
- He's an old acquaintance...

620
00:44:02,673 --> 00:44:05,267
...by the name of Lefreeze.
- As in the Lefreeze comet...

621
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:09,071
...my parents told us about?
- He just froze half our town.

622
00:44:09,279 --> 00:44:11,907
I've never seen so much ice.

623
00:44:12,116 --> 00:44:15,017
- Hence the name.
- What does he have against you?

624
00:44:15,219 --> 00:44:16,686
Besides that list, of course.

625
00:44:16,887 --> 00:44:18,411
Oh, it's a long story...

626
00:44:18,622 --> 00:44:21,819
...but he's not looking to exchange
Christmas cards, I can assure you.

627
00:44:22,026 --> 00:44:25,393
- He doesn't look very friendly.
- He's all bark and no bite.

628
00:44:25,596 --> 00:44:28,588
Is there another way
around the square?

629
00:44:28,799 --> 00:44:31,461
Yeah, but, they're in the way.

630
00:44:32,403 --> 00:44:35,600
Looks like my crew will have
to pick me up here, then.

631
00:44:35,806 --> 00:44:38,741
Good thing I've got a
tracking device on the sleigh.

632
00:44:40,144 --> 00:44:41,873
Can we get a picture of that too?

633
00:44:44,748 --> 00:44:45,737
Darn.

634
00:44:45,949 --> 00:44:48,383
Help! Let me out!

635
00:44:48,585 --> 00:44:51,884
Somebody? Anybody?

636
00:44:55,659 --> 00:44:58,685
Hey, wait a minute.

637
00:45:04,668 --> 00:45:08,570
Magic, huh?
All right, it's worth a try.

638
00:45:08,772 --> 00:45:11,866
Open sesame.

639
00:45:16,113 --> 00:45:17,671
Hey, what do you know?

640
00:45:17,881 --> 00:45:20,281
Maybe there is
something to this magic.

641
00:45:22,086 --> 00:45:24,850
- Santa, up here!
- Catch the rope!

642
00:45:25,389 --> 00:45:28,051
Well, that's my ride.
Thank goodness.

643
00:45:28,258 --> 00:45:30,123
Wait a sec. What about my picture?

644
00:45:30,327 --> 00:45:32,795
I'm very sorry,
but I've got a big night ahead of me.

645
00:45:32,996 --> 00:45:34,725
Adiós and adieu.

646
00:45:34,932 --> 00:45:36,422
Climb the rope. You can make it.

647
00:45:36,633 --> 00:45:39,295
That's it, keep coming.

648
00:45:41,038 --> 00:45:43,632
I had to eat those donuts.

649
00:45:43,841 --> 00:45:45,570
- Keep climbing, Santa.
- Come on, Santa.

650
00:45:45,776 --> 00:45:47,710
- Don't stop.
- Guys:

651
00:45:50,180 --> 00:45:53,115
I can't believe it. There he is.

652
00:45:57,421 --> 00:46:00,857
- Oh, yes, and bull's-eye.
- Yeah!

653
00:46:01,058 --> 00:46:02,218
Nice shot, boss.

654
00:46:08,866 --> 00:46:15,795
- Santa, are you okay?
- I like cocoa better than eggnog.

655
00:46:16,006 --> 00:46:18,133
Maybe you should just rest a bit.

656
00:46:18,342 --> 00:46:22,039
- Hey, boss, he went down over there.
- Yeah, let's go get him.

657
00:46:22,246 --> 00:46:24,305
Wait a minute.
Something's not right here.

658
00:46:24,515 --> 00:46:26,073
I don't know about those children.

659
00:46:26,283 --> 00:46:29,184
Yeah, boss,
but they're just a bunch of kids.

660
00:46:29,386 --> 00:46:31,354
Yeah, just little kids, like mini-crackers.

661
00:46:31,555 --> 00:46:33,648
They shot him out of
the sky with a laser.

662
00:46:33,857 --> 00:46:36,417
Who knows what they could do to us.

663
00:46:37,327 --> 00:46:39,056
Let me handle this.

664
00:46:40,998 --> 00:46:43,762
Nice job getting Santa Claus, children.

665
00:46:43,967 --> 00:46:45,229
We'd like to commend you.

666
00:46:45,435 --> 00:46:48,598
We've been trying for hundreds of years,
and you...

667
00:46:48,806 --> 00:46:52,105
You pulled it off in one night.
Congratulations.

668
00:46:52,309 --> 00:46:54,368
- Now hand him over.
- Go away!

669
00:46:54,578 --> 00:46:58,912
He's ours!
We caught him fair and square.

670
00:46:59,116 --> 00:47:01,550
All right, then, you leave me no choice...

671
00:47:01,752 --> 00:47:04,687
...but to bombard you
with these balls of snow.

672
00:47:06,890 --> 00:47:09,085
Did he just hit me with a snowball?

673
00:47:10,127 --> 00:47:14,359
You call that a snowball?
Here's a snowball.

674
00:47:15,532 --> 00:47:17,932
- Are you gonna help me or not here?
- Right away, sir.

675
00:47:18,135 --> 00:47:20,433
Yeah, they're just a bunch of kids.

676
00:47:20,637 --> 00:47:23,401
- Take that!
- Yeah, hey, try this on for size.

677
00:47:23,607 --> 00:47:25,006
Hand him over.

678
00:47:33,984 --> 00:47:36,077
I don't think you're getting the hint here.

679
00:47:36,286 --> 00:47:38,777
I came here for Santa. He's mine.

680
00:47:38,989 --> 00:47:41,583
- No, he's mine.
- Mine!

681
00:47:41,792 --> 00:47:42,986
- Mine!
- Mine!

682
00:47:43,193 --> 00:47:45,058
- I caught him first.
- I'm bigger than you.

683
00:47:45,262 --> 00:47:46,957
- And uglier.
- Well, there's no need...

684
00:47:47,164 --> 00:47:48,927
...to make this personal. Spread out.

685
00:47:49,132 --> 00:47:53,034
See if you can find any more of them.
I got things under control here.

686
00:47:54,071 --> 00:47:56,005
Look at all the snow.

687
00:47:56,206 --> 00:47:59,539
Don't think we're gonna have
another green Christmas this year.

688
00:48:00,410 --> 00:48:02,378
Gotcha!

689
00:48:02,846 --> 00:48:04,711
What on Earth is going on here?

690
00:48:04,915 --> 00:48:07,475
Wouldn't you like to know, sweetheart?

691
00:48:07,684 --> 00:48:09,345
Hey! Hey, get away from me.

692
00:48:10,621 --> 00:48:12,919
Back off, you overgrown snow cones.

693
00:48:13,123 --> 00:48:16,718
- Hey, my mother was a snow cone.
- That's right, she was.

694
00:48:16,927 --> 00:48:18,758
Now, you're coming with us.

695
00:48:20,464 --> 00:48:22,694
Help!

696
00:48:25,836 --> 00:48:27,770
- Hey, listen.
- What?

697
00:48:27,971 --> 00:48:30,201
- It's quiet.
- Maybe they've given up.

698
00:48:30,407 --> 00:48:33,240
Not likely. What's he up to?

699
00:48:33,443 --> 00:48:35,104
Drop your snowballs.

700
00:48:35,312 --> 00:48:39,339
I think we have something
you might be interested in.

701
00:48:42,152 --> 00:48:46,680
- Let her go right now.
- I'll trade you, her for him.

702
00:48:48,225 --> 00:48:50,216
This has gone far enough.
Now, let her go.

703
00:48:50,427 --> 00:48:52,088
- Santa.
- Okay, Freeze.

704
00:48:52,296 --> 00:48:56,255
- That's Lefreeze to you.
- Lefreeze, I'm sorry.

705
00:48:56,466 --> 00:49:01,267
No, you're not.
You've never been sorry, but you will be.

706
00:49:01,471 --> 00:49:03,234
Come on.

707
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:05,203
This isn't really about me.

708
00:49:05,409 --> 00:49:08,071
So how about we settle
this once and for all?

709
00:49:08,278 --> 00:49:09,540
Yeah.

710
00:49:09,746 --> 00:49:11,805
The time has come.

711
00:49:14,785 --> 00:49:18,050
I know what you've wanted
from me all these years.

712
00:49:21,992 --> 00:49:24,392
I stashed it here a while back.

713
00:49:24,594 --> 00:49:26,721
Yeah, yeah, here it is, a little dusty.

714
00:49:28,165 --> 00:49:31,100
Good thing I didn't let Barky
clean out the back seat.

715
00:49:33,837 --> 00:49:37,568
This is for you, Lefreeze.
Merry Christmas.

716
00:49:38,909 --> 00:49:41,844
Back it up, Red. You think you
can buy him off with a present?

717
00:49:42,045 --> 00:49:45,173
You think a knickknack
is enough to make him go away?

718
00:49:45,382 --> 00:49:46,542
You think...

719
00:49:46,750 --> 00:49:48,012
- Yeah!
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

720
00:49:48,218 --> 00:49:51,051
What kind of self-respecting
ice monster do you think...?

721
00:49:51,254 --> 00:49:52,619
Quiet, all of you.

722
00:49:52,823 --> 00:49:56,691
Maybe Lefreeze always wanted
a gift from Santa Claus.

723
00:49:56,893 --> 00:50:00,158
Maybe Lefreeze was
hurt he never got one.

724
00:50:01,198 --> 00:50:04,793
Boss, are you telling me
that's what this is all about?

725
00:50:05,002 --> 00:50:06,765
One undelivered Christmas present?

726
00:50:06,970 --> 00:50:08,835
You're a villain. Start acting like one.

727
00:50:09,039 --> 00:50:11,735
Yeah, what about that list?

728
00:50:11,942 --> 00:50:14,604
Yeah, the list. And your
unquenchable thirst for revenge?

729
00:50:14,811 --> 00:50:20,181
Okay, yeah, that list is all true,
but I mean, what is true anyway?

730
00:50:20,684 --> 00:50:24,051
What I think is true,
scientifically speaking to you...

731
00:50:24,254 --> 00:50:29,590
...I mean, may not be exactly true to me,
if you want to get all legal about it.

732
00:50:31,862 --> 00:50:35,525
Look, the honest side of it is, there's
really only one item on that list, okay?

733
00:50:35,732 --> 00:50:37,632
There, I said it.

734
00:50:38,435 --> 00:50:42,166
Jeez, I don't know about you guys,
but I'm feeling kind of used.

735
00:50:42,372 --> 00:50:43,703
Yeah, oh, brother.

736
00:50:43,907 --> 00:50:46,899
The whole thing is completely
embarrassing to be honest.

737
00:50:47,110 --> 00:50:49,578
Oh, come on.

738
00:50:51,248 --> 00:50:53,273
- All right, open it.
- Whatever.

739
00:50:53,483 --> 00:50:55,542
Yeah, take it.
I'm sick about the whole thing.

740
00:50:55,752 --> 00:50:59,313
- Can't even look at you anymore.
- Do you want this present or not?

741
00:51:00,557 --> 00:51:03,617
Golly, you shouldn't have.
Can I open it now?

742
00:51:03,827 --> 00:51:05,761
Well, it is Christmas.

743
00:51:10,967 --> 00:51:12,696
Yeah!

744
00:51:15,205 --> 00:51:18,504
It's just what I always wanted.

745
00:51:20,143 --> 00:51:22,611
I'm gonna call him Teddy.

746
00:51:22,813 --> 00:51:25,008
Well, this story has
taken an absurd turn.

747
00:51:25,215 --> 00:51:26,842
Oh, this is nothing.

748
00:51:29,319 --> 00:51:32,516
I think I've got a little
something for you three as well.

749
00:51:34,858 --> 00:51:37,258
- You can't buy us.
- Who do you think we are?

750
00:51:37,461 --> 00:51:40,328
- What do you got?
- Let me see here.

751
00:51:40,530 --> 00:51:43,158
I'm sure my reindeer won't miss these.

752
00:51:45,102 --> 00:51:47,434
A real carrot.

753
00:51:48,905 --> 00:51:52,397
- You know what? I can finally breathe.
- Gosh, Santa, a carrot.

754
00:51:52,609 --> 00:51:55,100
I don't know what to say here.

755
00:51:55,312 --> 00:51:56,870
Let me see if I can help you.

756
00:51:57,080 --> 00:52:00,277
Thank you, Santa.
We're really sorry about all this.

757
00:52:00,484 --> 00:52:03,180
- So no hard feelings, right?
- Of course not.

758
00:52:03,386 --> 00:52:05,081
'Tis the season to be jolly.

759
00:52:05,288 --> 00:52:07,222
I guess we've caused enough damage.

760
00:52:07,424 --> 00:52:09,221
Maybe we should just get going.

761
00:52:09,426 --> 00:52:12,327
Are you coming, Teddy?
Now, stay close to me.

762
00:52:12,529 --> 00:52:15,521
- It's gonna be cold.
- Goodbye, Santa.

763
00:52:15,732 --> 00:52:17,199
No hard feelings, huh, kids?

764
00:52:17,400 --> 00:52:20,801
If there's, you know, anything we can do,
just let us know.

765
00:52:21,004 --> 00:52:23,802
I think you've done enough.
Now, run along.

766
00:52:24,007 --> 00:52:25,736
Gee, thanks, Santa.

767
00:52:25,942 --> 00:52:28,809
I hope to see you next year.

768
00:52:33,016 --> 00:52:37,043
He just needed a little attention, Barky.
Get those reindeer in gear.

769
00:52:37,254 --> 00:52:39,051
Aye-aye, captain.

770
00:52:39,256 --> 00:52:43,488
Hey, Santa, I'm sorry for knocking you
out of the sky and everything.

771
00:52:43,693 --> 00:52:45,854
- I guess I got carried away.
- Forget about it.

772
00:52:46,062 --> 00:52:49,896
