see, and he hates Santa Claus.

820
00:56:42,699 --> 00:56:44,690
Least he used to.
He came here to get him...

821
00:56:44,901 --> 00:56:47,096
Sounds like one nifty dream, son.

822
00:56:47,303 --> 00:56:51,399
I know what it sounds like,
but it actually happened.

823
00:56:53,710 --> 00:56:54,938
Look, I'll prove it.

824
00:56:55,145 --> 00:56:58,706
Oh, no, my camera. What happened?

825
00:56:58,915 --> 00:57:02,681
Oh, the camera must've broke when
we were having that snowball fight.

826
00:57:02,886 --> 00:57:05,013
Maybe it was just a dream.

827
00:57:05,221 --> 00:57:09,749
Well, whatever it was, if you want proof
Santa exists, just look under the tree.

828
00:57:12,729 --> 00:57:15,027
From Santa, son.

829
00:57:16,433 --> 00:57:19,596
Oh, cool. A chess set, yeah.

830
00:57:19,803 --> 00:57:22,636
Oh, it's just what I asked him for.

831
00:57:22,839 --> 00:57:26,605
Well, not exactly what I asked him for.

832
00:57:26,810 --> 00:57:29,370
This is way better.

833
00:57:40,156 --> 00:57:44,058
<i>Santa has returned.</i>
<i>Santa has returned.</i>

